1
00:00:05,220 --> 00:00:07,540
=Live and Love S2=
=Watch Live and Love With Us=

2
00:00:15,120 --> 00:00:16,440
(Liang Tian, guest on Love Actually S4)
Hi everyone.

3
00:00:16,440 --> 00:00:18,230
(Sun Leyan, guest on Signal of the Heart S7)
EP 2 of Live and Love is back.

4
00:00:18,240 --> 00:00:20,080
Alright, let's get pumped up.

5
00:00:20,080 --> 00:00:21,000
Roll up our sleeves.

6
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:21,960
(Time to review)
Let me

7
00:00:21,960 --> 00:00:22,320
help you.

8
00:00:22,320 --> 00:00:22,960
Sleeves first.

9
00:00:22,960 --> 00:00:23,640
You roll mine up.

10
00:00:23,640 --> 00:00:24,440
Okay.

11
00:00:24,440 --> 00:00:24,880
Alright.

12
00:00:24,880 --> 00:00:26,400
Then I'll feed you a carrot.

13
00:00:26,400 --> 00:00:28,020
(You're picking this up fast)

14
00:00:28,520 --> 00:00:30,440
(Back to business)
Let's go, episode two

15
00:00:30,440 --> 00:00:31,320
starts now.

16
00:00:31,720 --> 00:00:34,920
(Balance Zone; Dining Room; Water Arena)
Welcome to Balance Island's water arena.

17
00:00:35,240 --> 00:00:36,120
Game on.

18
00:00:36,120 --> 00:00:37,920
The battle begins.

19
00:00:37,920 --> 00:00:40,200
This match is a solo competition.

20
00:00:40,200 --> 00:00:43,280
Men and women will compete separately.

21
00:00:43,280 --> 00:00:44,640
Every person fights for themselves.

22
00:00:45,320 --> 00:00:46,560
The women too?

23
00:00:46,560 --> 00:00:48,080
(Everyone's competing)

24
00:00:48,080 --> 00:00:48,840
Solo battle.

25
00:00:48,840 --> 00:00:49,200
Yeah.

26
00:00:49,200 --> 00:00:50,680
Yeah, everyone's got to compete.

27
00:00:50,680 --> 00:00:52,640
The winning man and woman

28
00:00:52,640 --> 00:00:56,240
will earn the right to plan the first date

29
00:00:56,240 --> 00:00:59,480
and assign partners.

30
00:00:59,820 --> 00:01:01,400
(Battle for power)
They get to decide.

31
00:01:01,400 --> 00:01:02,640
They can play matchmaker.

32
00:01:02,640 --> 00:01:03,000
Exactly.

33
00:01:03,100 --> 00:01:04,180
(It's getting interesting)

34
00:01:04,760 --> 00:01:05,000
I am

35
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:05,960
going to win.

36
00:01:06,120 --> 00:01:07,200
I want to win the game.

37
00:01:07,200 --> 00:01:09,280
That way, I get some say in what happens.

38
00:01:09,280 --> 00:01:10,720
When faced with competition,

39
00:01:10,720 --> 00:01:12,480
we all show our wild side.

40
00:01:12,520 --> 00:01:14,360
I'm determined to seize this chance

41
00:01:14,360 --> 00:01:15,200
to prove myself.

42
00:01:15,600 --> 00:01:16,680
They're ready to fight.

43
00:01:16,680 --> 00:01:17,680
It's gonna be intense.

44
00:01:18,760 --> 00:01:19,840
For me, this game

45
00:01:19,840 --> 00:01:20,920
is pretty challenging.

46
00:01:22,160 --> 00:01:23,960
Because my balance point is high.

47
00:01:23,960 --> 00:01:24,920
And the first player is

48
00:01:24,920 --> 00:01:26,440
Jiayi, which makes me more nervous.

49
00:01:26,440 --> 00:01:28,200
I'm so afraid she'll fall into the water.

50
00:01:28,360 --> 00:01:29,280
What are you doing?

51
00:01:30,560 --> 00:01:31,920
Step over my head.

52
00:01:32,260 --> 00:01:33,920
(Paving the way for love)

53
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:35,040
Pulling that move?

54
00:01:35,320 --> 00:01:36,000
Every single one

55
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:37,200
of his words and actions

56
00:01:37,200 --> 00:01:38,760
could catch you off guard.

57
00:01:38,760 --> 00:01:40,720
"Step over my head.

58
00:01:40,720 --> 00:01:42,560
Let me be your stepping stone."

59
00:01:42,560 --> 00:01:43,100
What is this?

60
00:01:43,100 --> 00:01:44,280
It's the pledge of allegiance.

61
00:01:44,280 --> 00:01:45,660
(Style can't be wasted)

62
00:01:47,080 --> 00:01:48,000
Step on my foot.

63
00:01:49,340 --> 00:01:51,500
(So sweet)

64
00:01:55,240 --> 00:01:56,640
Don't rush.

65
00:01:56,640 --> 00:01:58,120
You'll have your chance.

66
00:01:58,120 --> 00:02:01,600
Yeah, Yanting's waiting.

67
00:02:01,920 --> 00:02:03,200
He's been waiting forever.

68
00:02:04,480 --> 00:02:05,800
When Jiayi started the game,

69
00:02:05,800 --> 00:02:07,240
I honestly didn't think too much.

70
00:02:07,240 --> 00:02:08,520
I just wanted to make sure

71
00:02:08,520 --> 00:02:10,240
she got through my part safely.

72
00:02:11,620 --> 00:02:13,020
(Approved)

73
00:02:13,040 --> 00:02:13,880
Very good.

74
00:02:16,960 --> 00:02:17,880
Hold on tight.

75
00:02:17,880 --> 00:02:18,920
You can pass now.

76
00:02:20,280 --> 00:02:21,320
She hugged him.

77
00:02:22,080 --> 00:02:23,960
He didn't even dare to look at her.

78
00:02:24,360 --> 00:02:26,760
(Pretending to stay calm)
Such steady eyes, huh, Yanting?

79
00:02:26,920 --> 00:02:28,280
He didn't even glance at her.

80
00:02:28,280 --> 00:02:29,960
Is he shy or what?

81
00:02:29,960 --> 00:02:30,160
He...

82
00:02:30,160 --> 00:02:30,760
He's flushed.

83
00:02:30,760 --> 00:02:31,960
Look, even his arms are red.

84
00:02:31,960 --> 00:02:33,000
Yeah, he's nervous.

85
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:34,000
His whole face is red.

86
00:02:35,160 --> 00:02:37,240
When Jiayi walked past me,

87
00:02:37,240 --> 00:02:38,800
my heartbeat sped up a bit.

88
00:02:38,800 --> 00:02:41,760
Maybe because we were so close.

89
00:02:41,760 --> 00:02:43,880
It made my heart pound harder.

90
00:02:45,520 --> 00:02:46,840
You can tell he's nervous.

91
00:02:47,360 --> 00:02:48,320
Check who's next.

92
00:02:52,560 --> 00:02:53,480
She went by so fast.

93
00:02:53,480 --> 00:02:54,200
(Agile)

94
00:02:54,200 --> 00:02:54,680
Impressive.

95
00:02:54,680 --> 00:02:55,800
Like walking on solid ground.

96
00:02:55,800 --> 00:02:56,920
She walked straight through.

97
00:02:56,920 --> 00:02:57,640
Yeah.

98
00:02:57,840 --> 00:02:58,800
That's impressive.

99
00:02:58,800 --> 00:02:59,560
She's graceful.

100
00:02:59,600 --> 00:03:01,600
I think I might have an edge here.

101
00:03:01,600 --> 00:03:02,680
I'm smaller,

102
00:03:02,680 --> 00:03:04,480
so my center of gravity is lower.

103
00:03:05,760 --> 00:03:06,720
Center of gravity.

104
00:03:11,460 --> 00:03:13,700
(Shipping)

105
00:03:13,720 --> 00:03:15,000
Slow motion.

106
00:03:19,160 --> 00:03:21,040
I noticed Zhao Enda

107
00:03:21,040 --> 00:03:21,880
won't look at anyone.

108
00:03:21,900 --> 00:03:22,480
(Avoid)
Yeah.

109
00:03:22,480 --> 00:03:24,760
He's staying put
like a solid timber post.

110
00:03:24,760 --> 00:03:25,720
(A dependable post)

111
00:03:25,920 --> 00:03:26,800
See who's next.

112
00:03:26,800 --> 00:03:27,480
Yan.

113
00:03:27,720 --> 00:03:28,520
I'm here.

114
00:03:30,640 --> 00:03:32,880
(Here comes the show)
The wolf-dog's already locked in.

115
00:03:33,080 --> 00:03:34,200
Wolf-dog and big cat.

116
00:03:38,760 --> 00:03:40,280
She's pretty petite.

117
00:03:40,280 --> 00:03:41,040
Right.

118
00:03:41,040 --> 00:03:41,840
She moved so fast.

119
00:03:46,680 --> 00:03:47,440
Heads up.

120
00:03:48,920 --> 00:03:49,800
Eyes met.

121
00:03:51,640 --> 00:03:52,720
He cracked a smile.

122
00:03:52,720 --> 00:03:53,820
(Couldn't hold it in)

123
00:03:54,160 --> 00:03:55,760
He's the only one who made eye contact

124
00:03:55,760 --> 00:03:57,680
and couldn't help smiling.

125
00:03:58,540 --> 00:03:59,520
Even without eye contact,

126
00:03:59,520 --> 00:04:01,500
(Seeing through)
his grin nearly reached his ears.

127
00:04:01,520 --> 00:04:02,680
He couldn't stop smiling.

128
00:04:03,620 --> 00:04:04,980
(Pure happiness)

129
00:04:06,200 --> 00:04:07,280
(Peeping)
His expression.

130
00:04:08,280 --> 00:04:09,080
Walk on your own.

131
00:04:09,080 --> 00:04:09,880
How?

132
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:11,480
Wait.

133
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:13,480
Wait.

134
00:04:22,780 --> 00:04:24,100
(Didn't know you could play it like this!)

135
00:04:26,600 --> 00:04:27,280
This…

136
00:04:27,520 --> 00:04:30,800
I take back what I said in the last ep.

137
00:04:30,800 --> 00:04:31,320
Seriously.

138
00:04:31,750 --> 00:04:33,560
(Our comment on Xiaofan)
He's a bit careless.

139
00:04:33,560 --> 00:04:34,920
Yeah, I think so too.

140
00:04:34,920 --> 00:04:35,880
He really is.

141
00:04:35,880 --> 00:04:37,020
(Plot twist)

142
00:04:37,360 --> 00:04:38,400
Even though he fell down,

143
00:04:38,400 --> 00:04:39,680
somehow it felt like he still won.

144
00:04:39,680 --> 00:04:40,320
Agreed.

145
00:04:40,320 --> 00:04:41,720
Yeah, he won.

146
00:04:41,720 --> 00:04:43,640
Xiaofan, oh, Xiaofan.

147
00:04:44,440 --> 00:04:45,400
You're no ordinary guy.

148
00:04:46,740 --> 00:04:48,540
(He's got skills)

149
00:04:48,760 --> 00:04:50,080
Now we're moving on

150
00:04:50,080 --> 00:04:52,600
to round two of women's challenge.

151
00:04:52,600 --> 00:04:54,520
Log bridge betting race.

152
00:04:55,280 --> 00:04:57,400
Ladies, please stand on the bridge.

153
00:04:57,880 --> 00:05:00,600
You can pick which guy you think will win

154
00:05:00,960 --> 00:05:02,040
the competition.

155
00:05:02,040 --> 00:05:04,520
If your bet wins,

156
00:05:04,520 --> 00:05:06,480
you get an extra three points.

157
00:05:07,320 --> 00:05:09,560
But it depends on
whether she's playing for points,

158
00:05:09,560 --> 00:05:11,440
(Points? Feelings?)
or showing interest.

159
00:05:11,440 --> 00:05:12,040
Right.

160
00:05:13,200 --> 00:05:14,680
Huang Jiawei.

161
00:05:16,760 --> 00:05:19,320
A slight smile appears on his face.

162
00:05:19,640 --> 00:05:20,240
Michael.

163
00:05:21,920 --> 00:05:23,320
I didn't expect Yang

164
00:05:23,320 --> 00:05:25,000
to bet on me.

165
00:05:25,240 --> 00:05:26,240
I bet on Lu Yanting.

166
00:05:29,040 --> 00:05:30,400
She didn't pick me.

167
00:05:30,880 --> 00:05:32,080
I'm really kinda heartbroken.

168
00:05:32,400 --> 00:05:34,480
(Putting the game first)
They wanted to earn points.

169
00:05:34,760 --> 00:05:35,360
She didn't...

170
00:05:35,360 --> 00:05:36,800
She wasn't in a rush to show

171
00:05:36,800 --> 00:05:37,840
her affection.

172
00:05:38,040 --> 00:05:39,560
Win first, win big.

173
00:05:42,480 --> 00:05:44,800
I think it's probably hard for Xiaofan.

174
00:05:45,200 --> 00:05:45,840
He's too huge.

175
00:05:47,280 --> 00:05:48,000
No.

176
00:05:56,320 --> 00:05:57,880
Feels like a truck coming.

177
00:05:58,380 --> 00:05:59,000
If I step back,

178
00:05:59,000 --> 00:05:59,640
(Truck mode)
I

179
00:05:59,640 --> 00:06:00,360
will fall.

180
00:06:00,360 --> 00:06:00,760
Don't.

181
00:06:00,760 --> 00:06:01,440
I'll walk

182
00:06:01,440 --> 00:06:02,080
from behind.

183
00:06:02,080 --> 00:06:02,760
Behind me?

184
00:06:02,760 --> 00:06:03,480
You sure?

185
00:06:03,480 --> 00:06:05,200
I'll probably fall forward.

186
00:06:22,040 --> 00:06:23,520
What's that supposed to mean?

187
00:06:23,920 --> 00:06:24,560
I don't get it.

188
00:06:24,560 --> 00:06:25,740
(Beyond my dating knowledge)

189
00:06:26,040 --> 00:06:27,640
You've done this too many times, sir.

190
00:06:27,800 --> 00:06:28,260
Yeah.

191
00:06:28,260 --> 00:06:29,540
(Seriously?)
Isn't it too much?

192
00:06:29,540 --> 00:06:30,400
Yeah, it is.

193
00:06:30,400 --> 00:06:31,320
Right?

194
00:06:31,800 --> 00:06:32,440
He just couldn't

195
00:06:32,440 --> 00:06:33,720
(Trying to back you up)
get past her.

196
00:06:33,720 --> 00:06:34,040
Right?

197
00:06:34,320 --> 00:06:36,040
(Let me play along)
Oh, is that so?

198
00:06:36,600 --> 00:06:38,920
(Explaining)
Playing some kind of word game here.

199
00:06:39,400 --> 00:06:39,950
Alright then.

200
00:06:39,950 --> 00:06:40,850
(Don't get it, but respect)

201
00:06:41,120 --> 00:06:41,600
Go.

202
00:06:41,600 --> 00:06:42,800
Come on!

203
00:06:44,240 --> 00:06:45,520
Jia moved fast.

204
00:06:45,520 --> 00:06:47,320
And he's steady too.

205
00:06:47,320 --> 00:06:47,720
Yeah.

206
00:06:58,080 --> 00:07:00,320
(How can someone mess up this badly...)
Seriously?

207
00:07:01,240 --> 00:07:02,200
Zhang Zizheng, go down.

208
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:07,560
Move!

209
00:07:08,400 --> 00:07:09,240
Nice job.

210
00:07:10,680 --> 00:07:10,960
Nice.

211
00:07:10,960 --> 00:07:12,280
Looks like two people fell in.

212
00:07:12,280 --> 00:07:13,120
Actually, it's three.

213
00:07:13,120 --> 00:07:14,160
Yeah.

214
00:07:14,760 --> 00:07:15,720
That works.

215
00:07:15,720 --> 00:07:17,280
(Envious)

216
00:07:17,280 --> 00:07:18,480
That's amazing.

217
00:07:18,480 --> 00:07:20,200
I'll be the one looking out for my girl.

218
00:07:20,200 --> 00:07:21,180
(Protecting)

219
00:07:27,320 --> 00:07:28,320
Security.

220
00:07:28,320 --> 00:07:29,960
Good.

221
00:07:33,400 --> 00:07:33,840
You okay?

222
00:07:34,800 --> 00:07:36,680
So in the end, whether he wins

223
00:07:36,680 --> 00:07:37,760
or loses

224
00:07:37,760 --> 00:07:38,880
might not be that important.

225
00:07:38,880 --> 00:07:39,480
Yeah.

226
00:07:39,880 --> 00:07:41,960
What really matters is what happens

227
00:07:41,960 --> 00:07:43,400
(I care for you)
beyond the rules.

228
00:07:43,400 --> 00:07:45,740
Honestly, that's nice.

229
00:07:45,740 --> 00:07:46,680
(Felt love beyond the rules)

230
00:07:46,680 --> 00:07:48,280
A true gentleman.

231
00:07:49,780 --> 00:07:51,660
(Lost points, won love)

232
00:07:52,440 --> 00:07:53,720
They all have umbrellas.

233
00:07:53,960 --> 00:07:54,680
If I hadn't come,

234
00:07:54,680 --> 00:07:55,740
wouldn't that be awkward?

235
00:07:55,740 --> 00:07:56,240
Let me hold

236
00:07:56,240 --> 00:07:56,760
the umbrella.

237
00:07:56,760 --> 00:07:57,520
No, leave it to me.

238
00:07:57,520 --> 00:07:58,400
Alright.

239
00:07:58,400 --> 00:08:00,380
(Who could resist shipping them?)

240
00:08:00,620 --> 00:08:01,440
Can't you step under

241
00:08:01,440 --> 00:08:02,400
the umbrella yourself?

242
00:08:02,400 --> 00:08:04,360
Why do you have to make it a show?

243
00:08:04,360 --> 00:08:06,580
(Just trying to start a conversation)

244
00:08:06,720 --> 00:08:08,440
Islander Yang Tinghong,

245
00:08:09,040 --> 00:08:10,120
Lu Yanting,

246
00:08:10,320 --> 00:08:12,120
congratulations, you've earned

247
00:08:12,120 --> 00:08:14,040
the right to plan the first date.

248
00:08:14,320 --> 00:08:15,640
That's awesome.

249
00:08:16,400 --> 00:08:16,880
So now,

250
00:08:16,880 --> 00:08:18,880
they get to choose

251
00:08:18,880 --> 00:08:21,240
which guy and girl
will go on the date, right?

252
00:08:21,240 --> 00:08:22,600
(On-Island Date Arrangement)

253
00:08:22,600 --> 00:08:24,960
On-island date arrangement.

254
00:08:25,440 --> 00:08:26,920
How will they set this up?

255
00:08:26,920 --> 00:08:28,340
(On-Island Date Arrangement)
Here we go.

256
00:08:31,040 --> 00:08:33,520
You can pick from any of the twelve islanders

257
00:08:33,520 --> 00:08:35,040
to go on an on-island date.

258
00:08:35,040 --> 00:08:37,200
One of the date spots is the rooftop.

259
00:08:37,200 --> 00:08:39,320
(Sunset On The Rooftop)

260
00:08:39,330 --> 00:08:39,960
Cliffside terrace.

261
00:08:39,960 --> 00:08:42,380
(Cliffside Terrace)

262
00:08:42,400 --> 00:08:43,600
And coconut grove lawn.

263
00:08:43,600 --> 00:08:45,860
(Coconut Grove Lawn)

264
00:08:46,920 --> 00:08:49,160
(Limited date slots)
Some guests can't go on dates.

265
00:08:49,160 --> 00:08:50,720
Only six people can.

266
00:08:51,080 --> 00:08:52,600
So there are three couples in total.

267
00:08:52,600 --> 00:08:54,080
Who gets the last chance?

268
00:08:54,080 --> 00:08:55,980
(Who will get the third date?)

269
00:09:01,440 --> 00:09:03,520
And what about me?

270
00:09:07,560 --> 00:09:08,520
Okay.

271
00:09:08,640 --> 00:09:09,920
Then it's happily decided.

272
00:09:09,920 --> 00:09:10,560
Yes.

273
00:09:11,720 --> 00:09:12,120
Yes.

274
00:09:12,120 --> 00:09:12,600
Congrats.

275
00:09:12,800 --> 00:09:14,240
The third couple

276
00:09:14,240 --> 00:09:15,440
is also happily decided.

277
00:09:15,720 --> 00:09:17,000
They get to decide?

278
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:17,640
(Realized)
Yeah.

279
00:09:17,640 --> 00:09:19,200
Right, they have the right.

280
00:09:19,480 --> 00:09:21,440
I'm pretty sure it'll be...

281
00:09:21,440 --> 00:09:23,320
(Huang Jiawei, Zhu Huiyan)
Jiawei and Yan.

282
00:09:23,320 --> 00:09:23,800
Yeah.

283
00:09:23,800 --> 00:09:25,320
A truly respectable opponent.

284
00:09:25,320 --> 00:09:26,360
Right.

285
00:09:26,920 --> 00:09:27,760
Why is it Yan?

286
00:09:27,760 --> 00:09:28,480
Yan.

287
00:09:28,960 --> 00:09:29,590
She's gorgeous.

288
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:32,360
Why is it Yan?

289
00:09:33,040 --> 00:09:34,440
There are three pairs.

290
00:09:36,440 --> 00:09:38,680
Wasn't she close with

291
00:09:38,680 --> 00:09:39,440
that person?

292
00:09:42,640 --> 00:09:43,480
He didn't choose

293
00:09:43,480 --> 00:09:44,080
Jiayi.

294
00:09:44,080 --> 00:09:44,880
He didn't?

295
00:09:46,720 --> 00:09:47,640
He chose Yan.

296
00:09:48,320 --> 00:09:49,560
I really didn't see that coming.

297
00:09:50,220 --> 00:09:51,980
(Has everyone lost their minds?)

298
00:09:52,060 --> 00:09:53,120
(Come on, wake up!)

299
00:09:53,120 --> 00:09:54,480
Can you use your brains for a sec?

300
00:09:54,720 --> 00:09:56,160
These "Three Fools".

301
00:09:56,440 --> 00:09:58,560
"Three Fools" causing chaos
on Balance Island.

302
00:09:59,960 --> 00:10:01,280
Wait, that's not right.

303
00:10:01,280 --> 00:10:02,160
Then what is it?

304
00:10:02,380 --> 00:10:03,480
(Let it go)
Stop guessing.

305
00:10:03,480 --> 00:10:05,560
So they want the three of them together?

306
00:10:05,960 --> 00:10:06,360
No.

307
00:10:06,360 --> 00:10:07,560
There's no such date.

308
00:10:07,560 --> 00:10:08,120
Ridiculous.

309
00:10:08,960 --> 00:10:09,880
(Clueless)
Use your brain.

310
00:10:10,400 --> 00:10:10,800
I think

311
00:10:10,800 --> 00:10:11,520
those three guys

312
00:10:11,520 --> 00:10:12,760
can perfectly act out

313
00:10:12,760 --> 00:10:13,920
many boys'

314
00:10:13,920 --> 00:10:15,200
inner drama.

315
00:10:15,200 --> 00:10:16,000
Yeah, absolutely.

316
00:10:16,000 --> 00:10:17,220
(Inner Drama: Do I have a chance?)

317
00:10:17,700 --> 00:10:18,620
(Man, he's so lucky.)

318
00:10:19,180 --> 00:10:21,220
(Maybe I just don't understand love.)

319
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:25,840
Hello.

320
00:10:28,320 --> 00:10:29,320
Hello.

321
00:10:32,600 --> 00:10:33,520
Seriously?

322
00:10:33,800 --> 00:10:34,800
Nope.

323
00:10:34,800 --> 00:10:35,480
Not a chance.

324
00:10:35,800 --> 00:10:36,800
Hello.

325
00:10:38,720 --> 00:10:39,640
Hello.

326
00:10:40,800 --> 00:10:41,520
Hello.

327
00:10:41,670 --> 00:10:42,310
Editing.

328
00:10:42,310 --> 00:10:42,720
Hello.

329
00:10:42,750 --> 00:10:43,230
I got it.

330
00:10:43,230 --> 00:10:44,580
(You've mastered editing now.)

331
00:10:44,840 --> 00:10:45,520
That's romantic.

332
00:10:46,400 --> 00:10:47,920
Feels like we're having a picnic.

333
00:10:47,920 --> 00:10:48,640
Yeah.

334
00:10:49,960 --> 00:10:52,240
We can choose from twelve islanders

335
00:10:52,240 --> 00:10:53,920
to make three pairs.

336
00:10:54,000 --> 00:10:57,440
I want to give this chance to Jiawei.

337
00:10:57,440 --> 00:10:58,120
Sure.

338
00:10:58,400 --> 00:10:59,480
Then…

339
00:10:59,480 --> 00:11:00,760
Which one of your best friends

340
00:11:00,760 --> 00:11:03,400
you think is fit for this date?

341
00:11:03,400 --> 00:11:05,120
Alright, let's go with Yan.

342
00:11:05,660 --> 00:11:06,290
(Rooftop: Yang Tinghong)

343
00:11:06,300 --> 00:11:06,820
(Terrace: Lu Yanting)

344
00:11:06,820 --> 00:11:07,600
(Lawn: Huang Jiawei, Zhu Huiyan)

345
00:11:07,600 --> 00:11:08,200
All set.

346
00:11:08,960 --> 00:11:09,680
Good buddy.

347
00:11:09,680 --> 00:11:10,990
(Good buddy)
He's been working hard

348
00:11:10,990 --> 00:11:11,680
in the game.

349
00:11:12,360 --> 00:11:14,320
Didn't expect my first date to be you.

350
00:11:15,160 --> 00:11:15,760
How many...?

351
00:11:15,760 --> 00:11:16,160
Kidding.

352
00:11:16,160 --> 00:11:16,940
I'm expecting you.

353
00:11:20,520 --> 00:11:21,640
He's kidding.

354
00:11:22,040 --> 00:11:23,280
What's your first impression

355
00:11:23,280 --> 00:11:23,900
on me?

356
00:11:23,900 --> 00:11:25,000
The very first impression.

357
00:11:25,600 --> 00:11:27,280
You look like Shawn Yue.

358
00:11:27,960 --> 00:11:28,880
Do I? Really?

359
00:11:29,360 --> 00:11:29,880
Yeah, you do.

360
00:11:33,840 --> 00:11:35,000
Big eyes.

361
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:38,200
And your skin's a bit tan too.

362
00:11:38,840 --> 00:11:39,280
No one's

363
00:11:39,280 --> 00:11:40,160
ever said that?

364
00:11:40,160 --> 00:11:40,980
No, most people say

365
00:11:40,980 --> 00:11:42,600
I look a lot like Bosco Wong.

366
00:11:42,600 --> 00:11:44,900
(Yeah, kind of does)

367
00:11:44,920 --> 00:11:45,320
True.

368
00:11:45,320 --> 00:11:46,840
You look more like him with glasses on.

369
00:11:46,840 --> 00:11:47,360
Right?

370
00:11:48,640 --> 00:11:50,220
Bosco's eyes aren't even as big as his.

371
00:11:52,220 --> 00:11:53,700
Do you believe in love at first sight?

372
00:11:55,700 --> 00:11:56,920
Yeah, I do.

373
00:11:56,920 --> 00:11:57,640
Do you?

374
00:11:58,760 --> 00:11:59,560
Yeah.

375
00:12:00,600 --> 00:12:02,160
(Direct question)
They're really open.

376
00:12:02,680 --> 00:12:04,520
How long do you think love lasts?

377
00:12:05,480 --> 00:12:06,640
I never thought about it.

378
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:09,840
Her questions are pretty sharp.

379
00:12:10,080 --> 00:12:10,880
I have a question.

380
00:12:10,880 --> 00:12:12,800
Have you thought about
reaching out to others?

381
00:12:13,360 --> 00:12:14,640
I've only known you for two days.

382
00:12:15,120 --> 00:12:16,280
You want the honest truth?

383
00:12:17,160 --> 00:12:17,960
You'd reach out...

384
00:12:17,960 --> 00:12:18,560
No.

385
00:12:18,560 --> 00:12:19,200
Just…

386
00:12:19,200 --> 00:12:20,240
I'm scared too.

387
00:12:20,240 --> 00:12:21,480
If I were to…

388
00:12:21,480 --> 00:12:22,280
(choose) you.

389
00:12:23,820 --> 00:12:24,840
You might feel pressured?

390
00:12:24,840 --> 00:12:26,060
(Got the hint)

391
00:12:27,480 --> 00:12:28,920
I do have feelings for you.

392
00:12:28,920 --> 00:12:29,560
But…

393
00:12:29,920 --> 00:12:31,820
If I tried connecting
with two people at once,

394
00:12:32,120 --> 00:12:33,360
I might get distracted.

395
00:12:35,320 --> 00:12:37,160
I'm not really following what he means.

396
00:12:37,160 --> 00:12:39,380
(Just say it straight)

397
00:12:39,720 --> 00:12:40,560
Thinking about her.

398
00:12:40,560 --> 00:12:41,440
Is that what you mean?

399
00:12:42,120 --> 00:12:43,160
So you'd never

400
00:12:43,160 --> 00:12:44,720
date two people at the same time.

401
00:12:44,720 --> 00:12:45,600
But, let's say…

402
00:12:45,600 --> 00:12:47,000
If I wasn't committed to you,

403
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:48,320
you'd start seeing someone else.

404
00:12:48,320 --> 00:12:49,000
Am I right?

405
00:12:49,280 --> 00:12:51,360
Her perception was...

406
00:12:51,360 --> 00:12:52,240
spot-on.

407
00:12:54,560 --> 00:12:56,400
He suddenly couldn't meet her eyes.

408
00:12:59,420 --> 00:13:00,540
(Nods)

409
00:13:00,560 --> 00:13:01,480
He's actually honest.

410
00:13:02,640 --> 00:13:04,720
So what's your definition of commitment?

411
00:13:11,080 --> 00:13:12,280
Two pros facing off.

412
00:13:14,240 --> 00:13:15,360
Can I throw a question back?

413
00:13:16,360 --> 00:13:17,860
Have you thought about seeing others?

414
00:13:18,560 --> 00:13:19,560
Me?

415
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:22,040
Honestly, yesterday I felt

416
00:13:22,040 --> 00:13:23,440
you didn't give me all your votes.

417
00:13:23,440 --> 00:13:24,240
I'm guessing.

418
00:13:24,600 --> 00:13:25,480
She nailed it.

419
00:13:27,140 --> 00:13:29,320
I didn't feel like
you'd give me all your votes either.

420
00:13:29,800 --> 00:13:30,400
Of course.

421
00:13:30,400 --> 00:13:31,120
I mean it.

422
00:13:31,120 --> 00:13:32,600
Same feeling here.

423
00:13:32,600 --> 00:13:33,280
Are you...

424
00:13:33,280 --> 00:13:35,360
So you're saying

425
00:13:35,360 --> 00:13:36,320
you didn't give me

426
00:13:36,320 --> 00:13:37,480
all your votes.

427
00:13:37,480 --> 00:13:38,760
And I wouldn't back you either.

428
00:13:38,760 --> 00:13:39,680
Is that how you see it?

429
00:13:39,680 --> 00:13:40,160
Am I right?

430
00:13:40,760 --> 00:13:41,400
Yes or no?

431
00:13:43,080 --> 00:13:43,760
So what?

432
00:13:45,500 --> 00:13:46,140
(Anxious)

433
00:13:46,160 --> 00:13:46,560
Stop.

434
00:13:46,560 --> 00:13:47,460
It's about to blow up.

435
00:13:48,200 --> 00:13:48,880
Drop it.

436
00:13:50,160 --> 00:13:51,520
Deep down, they all crave

437
00:13:51,520 --> 00:13:52,880
to be chosen without hesitation.

438
00:13:52,880 --> 00:13:53,200
Right.

439
00:13:53,200 --> 00:13:56,720
(Hiding feelings with a test)
But they themselves are...

440
00:13:56,720 --> 00:13:58,200
Maybe it's to give themselves

441
00:13:58,200 --> 00:13:59,640
a stronger sense of security

442
00:13:59,640 --> 00:14:02,080
or to avoid getting hurt too badly.

443
00:14:02,080 --> 00:14:03,920
(Not fully committed)
So when making choices,

444
00:14:04,560 --> 00:14:05,360
they left themselves

445
00:14:05,360 --> 00:14:08,480
another way out or backup plan.

446
00:14:08,480 --> 00:14:09,240
I think

447
00:14:09,240 --> 00:14:10,280
they want to be treated

448
00:14:10,280 --> 00:14:11,320
as the one and only.

449
00:14:11,320 --> 00:14:12,840
They lack a sense of security

450
00:14:12,840 --> 00:14:13,720
to some extent.

451
00:14:13,720 --> 00:14:16,060
(Agree)

452
00:14:16,840 --> 00:14:18,720
I think we are way too alike.

453
00:14:20,600 --> 00:14:21,920
She sneered.

454
00:14:21,920 --> 00:14:23,480
Yeah, she let out a cold laugh.

455
00:14:23,640 --> 00:14:24,980
I actually voted for someone else.

456
00:14:26,160 --> 00:14:26,620
That is

457
00:14:26,620 --> 00:14:27,000
normal.

458
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:27,800
Hear me out first.

459
00:14:27,800 --> 00:14:28,200
It's okay.

460
00:14:28,520 --> 00:14:29,120
But...

461
00:14:29,120 --> 00:14:29,680
A twist.

462
00:14:29,680 --> 00:14:30,840
I gave you two votes.

463
00:14:31,160 --> 00:14:31,700
Thank you.

464
00:14:31,700 --> 00:14:32,900
Did you only give me one vote?

465
00:14:33,960 --> 00:14:34,800
You gave me one vote?

466
00:14:34,800 --> 00:14:36,120
Why would you question me

467
00:14:36,120 --> 00:14:36,580
like that?

468
00:14:37,120 --> 00:14:37,760
And

469
00:14:38,320 --> 00:14:39,920
I'll cast all my votes for you.

470
00:14:40,920 --> 00:14:41,720
Today?

471
00:14:47,800 --> 00:14:49,240
Then I'm honestly really happy.

472
00:14:49,240 --> 00:14:50,120
Glad to hear that.

473
00:14:50,120 --> 00:14:51,000
Hope you're happy.

474
00:14:57,020 --> 00:14:57,800
They're on the same

475
00:14:57,800 --> 00:14:58,760
(Evenly matched)
level.

476
00:14:58,760 --> 00:14:59,760
Exactly.

477
00:14:59,760 --> 00:15:01,320
Now look at their conversation.

478
00:15:01,320 --> 00:15:02,660
It's always about asking questions

479
00:15:02,660 --> 00:15:03,960
at each other.

480
00:15:03,960 --> 00:15:05,600
Right after they get an answer,

481
00:15:05,600 --> 00:15:07,680
they'll throw the question right back.

482
00:15:08,000 --> 00:15:09,480
Do you believe in love at first sight?

483
00:15:09,560 --> 00:15:10,280
Do you?

484
00:15:10,520 --> 00:15:11,990
Have you thought about someone else?

485
00:15:12,080 --> 00:15:13,080
Have you thought about

486
00:15:13,080 --> 00:15:14,000
seeing someone else?

487
00:15:14,100 --> 00:15:15,280
Basically, everything he does,

488
00:15:15,280 --> 00:15:16,440
he wants the other person to

489
00:15:16,440 --> 00:15:17,880
(A clear answer)
respond in kind.

490
00:15:17,880 --> 00:15:19,080
I feel like he's always...

491
00:15:19,080 --> 00:15:20,320
Always testing the waters...

492
00:15:20,320 --> 00:15:20,760
He is.

493
00:15:20,760 --> 00:15:21,240
Yeah.

494
00:15:21,240 --> 00:15:21,880
And

495
00:15:21,880 --> 00:15:22,440
fishing.

496
00:15:22,800 --> 00:15:23,760
Maybe he wants

497
00:15:23,760 --> 00:15:24,680
a more certain answer.

498
00:15:24,680 --> 00:15:25,280
A sign.

499
00:15:25,280 --> 00:15:26,240
Yeah, exactly.

500
00:15:26,240 --> 00:15:26,920
It reminded me of

501
00:15:26,920 --> 00:15:27,840
a similar moment I had.

502
00:15:27,840 --> 00:15:28,840
Like, asking questions

503
00:15:29,360 --> 00:15:29,960
to Oscar.

504
00:15:29,960 --> 00:15:32,000
(Love needs careful confirmation)
But luckily,

505
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:32,880
he had a clear answer

506
00:15:32,880 --> 00:15:34,320
(It is the right answer)
ready.

507
00:15:34,320 --> 00:15:35,600
But if I met someone

508
00:15:35,600 --> 00:15:36,920
who was more...

509
00:15:36,920 --> 00:15:37,920
maybe a bit like me,

510
00:15:37,920 --> 00:15:39,820
wandering around and hesitant,

511
00:15:39,820 --> 00:15:40,720
we might end up having

512
00:15:40,720 --> 00:15:42,000
a conversation just like theirs.

513
00:15:42,000 --> 00:15:43,060
Neither of us

514
00:15:43,060 --> 00:15:44,080
would give it our all.

515
00:15:45,520 --> 00:15:46,440
In Love Actually S4,

516
00:15:46,440 --> 00:15:48,120
everyone's not that young anymore.

517
00:15:48,560 --> 00:15:49,420
We're in our thirties.

518
00:15:49,680 --> 00:15:51,600
From what I can remember,

519
00:15:51,600 --> 00:15:54,080
no one was being that straightforward.

520
00:15:54,080 --> 00:15:55,360
(Age makes you reserved)
No one

521
00:15:55,360 --> 00:15:56,760
asked direct questions like them.

522
00:15:56,760 --> 00:15:58,480
I feel like even in the end,

523
00:15:58,480 --> 00:15:59,760
it never really happened.

524
00:15:59,760 --> 00:16:01,120
We never really asked

525
00:16:01,400 --> 00:16:02,240
direct questions,

526
00:16:02,240 --> 00:16:03,300
like, if you choose me,

527
00:16:03,300 --> 00:16:04,140
then I'll choose you.

528
00:16:04,140 --> 00:16:05,280
Nothing like that happened.

529
00:16:05,280 --> 00:16:05,760
Yeah.

530
00:16:06,240 --> 00:16:08,200
So it really depends on

531
00:16:08,580 --> 00:16:10,280
(It's different for everyone)
personality.

532
00:16:10,280 --> 00:16:11,960
The great thing is

533
00:16:11,960 --> 00:16:14,480
their personalities match perfectly.

534
00:16:14,920 --> 00:16:15,280
Right.

535
00:16:15,280 --> 00:16:17,040
The two of them really are aligned.

536
00:16:17,040 --> 00:16:18,160
They're so alike.

537
00:16:18,160 --> 00:16:20,080
So maybe they just get each other.

538
00:16:20,080 --> 00:16:21,480
It's a rare, lucky connection.

539
00:16:21,480 --> 00:16:22,980
(It's lucky to meet similar souls.)

540
00:16:23,360 --> 00:16:24,320
But after this (date),

541
00:16:24,320 --> 00:16:25,800
someone's leaving today, right?

542
00:16:27,420 --> 00:16:29,300
(Who's going to be eliminated?)

543
00:16:29,320 --> 00:16:30,480
I feel like making noodles.

544
00:16:30,920 --> 00:16:32,320
Do we have any noodles?

545
00:16:33,480 --> 00:16:35,240
So who's your crush?

546
00:16:36,320 --> 00:16:37,340
That came out of nowhere.

547
00:16:37,640 --> 00:16:39,200
Your crush is Yan.

548
00:16:40,320 --> 00:16:42,440
I don't really have a clear favorite.

549
00:16:42,500 --> 00:16:44,540
(Seriously?)

550
00:16:44,540 --> 00:16:45,990
You fell into the water twice for her

551
00:16:45,990 --> 00:16:47,320
and you were so upfront.

552
00:16:47,320 --> 00:16:48,120
I honestly fell in

553
00:16:48,120 --> 00:16:49,400
by accident the second time.

554
00:16:49,720 --> 00:16:51,400
But you were still very direct.

555
00:16:51,800 --> 00:16:52,960
I just flipped a switch.

556
00:16:53,360 --> 00:16:54,440
(What switch?)
I'm confused

557
00:16:54,440 --> 00:16:56,560
I'm confused about Xiaofan.

558
00:16:56,560 --> 00:16:57,680
You did it for the drama?

559
00:16:57,680 --> 00:16:58,720
For the drama...

560
00:16:59,360 --> 00:17:00,520
It kind of makes me mad.

561
00:17:00,520 --> 00:17:01,080
(angry)

562
00:17:01,080 --> 00:17:01,720
Yeah.

563
00:17:02,480 --> 00:17:03,880
Half of it is

564
00:17:03,880 --> 00:17:04,840
out of curiosity.

565
00:17:04,840 --> 00:17:06,240
And the other half is for...

566
00:17:06,240 --> 00:17:07,480
(What's the other half?)

567
00:17:07,480 --> 00:17:07,890
The drama.

568
00:17:09,240 --> 00:17:10,040
You're so naughty.

569
00:17:11,040 --> 00:17:12,080
I can't read you anymore.

570
00:17:12,080 --> 00:17:13,560
(Hard to read)
Yi Xiaofan.

571
00:17:13,560 --> 00:17:15,200
I think even he himself

572
00:17:15,200 --> 00:17:16,400
can't fully explain it.

573
00:17:16,400 --> 00:17:17,720
Honestly speaking,

574
00:17:17,720 --> 00:17:19,520
he probably hasn't figured it out.

575
00:17:19,540 --> 00:17:20,440
(Trying to understand)

576
00:17:20,440 --> 00:17:21,840
(Failed)
He definitely hasn't.

577
00:17:22,360 --> 00:17:23,040
He's so playful.

578
00:17:23,040 --> 00:17:24,400
(Very playful)

579
00:17:24,400 --> 00:17:26,040
So you're just shy around her.

580
00:17:26,040 --> 00:17:26,440
No.

581
00:17:26,440 --> 00:17:27,240
I usually dodge

582
00:17:27,240 --> 00:17:28,360
everyone.

583
00:17:31,720 --> 00:17:33,120
But you're staring straight at her.

584
00:17:33,120 --> 00:17:33,920
Not with me.

585
00:17:34,220 --> 00:17:36,100
(Busted)

586
00:17:36,120 --> 00:17:37,120
That's hilarious.

587
00:17:37,120 --> 00:17:38,520
So far, I feel like

588
00:17:38,520 --> 00:17:41,080
(Always vague)
he won't commit to any relationship.

589
00:17:41,080 --> 00:17:42,800
I think he enjoys the push and pull.

590
00:17:42,800 --> 00:17:44,560
Like the way he's with Yan.

591
00:17:44,700 --> 00:17:46,220
Some people just like being ambiguous.

592
00:17:46,220 --> 00:17:47,640
(You can tell)

593
00:17:47,640 --> 00:17:48,920
But to be honest,

594
00:17:48,920 --> 00:17:50,480
I didn't vote for Yan yesterday.

595
00:17:50,960 --> 00:17:51,920
Pretty upfront about it.

596
00:17:52,720 --> 00:17:53,560
Not a single vote.

597
00:17:53,580 --> 00:17:55,060
(Boys are completely stunned)

598
00:17:55,480 --> 00:17:57,360
Boys are in total shock.

599
00:17:57,420 --> 00:17:58,760
(No one can figure out Yi Xiaofan)

600
00:17:58,800 --> 00:17:59,760
One vote for Chen Yijia.

601
00:17:59,760 --> 00:18:00,840
(Chen Yijia)

602
00:18:00,840 --> 00:18:01,280
Jiaming.

603
00:18:01,280 --> 00:18:02,880
(Zhan Jiaming)
He must've voted for Jiaming.

604
00:18:02,880 --> 00:18:03,480
Anyone else?

605
00:18:04,080 --> 00:18:04,720
Zhan Jiaming.

606
00:18:05,320 --> 00:18:06,280
He gave her two votes.

607
00:18:06,280 --> 00:18:06,880
Two votes.

608
00:18:06,880 --> 00:18:08,160
(Surprising)
What caught my attention

609
00:18:08,160 --> 00:18:08,840
was Miss Zhan.

610
00:18:11,280 --> 00:18:12,800
Miss Zhan can't figure you out.

611
00:18:12,800 --> 00:18:13,360
Miss Zhan.

612
00:18:13,360 --> 00:18:14,560
(Copying Miss Zhan)
Stop being curious.

613
00:18:14,760 --> 00:18:16,320
I feel like having scrambled eggs.

614
00:18:16,320 --> 00:18:17,520
You sure you want that?

615
00:18:17,520 --> 00:18:19,280
If I cook it, you better finish it.

616
00:18:24,200 --> 00:18:24,980
Zhang Zizheng.

617
00:18:24,980 --> 00:18:25,680
(Huh?)

618
00:18:25,680 --> 00:18:26,520
Again?

619
00:18:26,520 --> 00:18:27,280
(What's it about?)

620
00:18:27,280 --> 00:18:29,240
The main ingredient is egg.

621
00:18:29,240 --> 00:18:30,640
Then let's just improvise.

622
00:18:31,400 --> 00:18:32,680
This is insanely good.

623
00:18:33,640 --> 00:18:34,720
How long will this take?

624
00:18:35,160 --> 00:18:36,000
Ten minutes.

625
00:18:36,000 --> 00:18:36,960
The water's not boiled.

626
00:18:37,960 --> 00:18:39,320
It's boiling.

627
00:18:39,380 --> 00:18:40,880
(A date on the other side)

628
00:18:40,880 --> 00:18:41,980
(Relieved)
It takes time.

629
00:18:42,840 --> 00:18:43,440
Let me feel

630
00:18:43,440 --> 00:18:44,040
peace.

631
00:18:44,040 --> 00:18:45,760
(Take a break)
Confused by Xiaofan.

632
00:18:45,760 --> 00:18:46,640
I think his behavior

633
00:18:46,640 --> 00:18:48,960
can easily make girls misunderstand.

634
00:18:48,960 --> 00:18:49,240
Yeah.

635
00:18:49,240 --> 00:18:50,700
(Dating tip 1)
One misunderstanding

636
00:18:50,700 --> 00:18:51,320
leads to another.

637
00:18:51,320 --> 00:18:52,460
(Chain reaction)
That causes

638
00:18:52,460 --> 00:18:53,380
chaotic relationships

639
00:18:53,880 --> 00:18:55,560
(Confusion sets in)
and huge mix-ups

640
00:18:55,560 --> 00:18:56,160
in the end.

641
00:18:57,400 --> 00:18:58,800
From a girl's perspective,

642
00:18:58,800 --> 00:19:00,360
(Dislike)
I don't like that.

643
00:19:00,360 --> 00:19:01,920
I really hate that messy vibe.

644
00:19:01,920 --> 00:19:02,200
Because

645
00:19:02,200 --> 00:19:03,640
you can live in your own chaos,

646
00:19:03,640 --> 00:19:06,240
just don't drag me into it.

647
00:19:06,240 --> 00:19:08,160
Keep a clear mind
and a solid sense of self.

648
00:19:09,420 --> 00:19:10,700
(Let's keep watching)

649
00:19:10,840 --> 00:19:12,320
I didn't pick you, would you be upset?

650
00:19:12,600 --> 00:19:13,280
Of course not.

651
00:19:15,520 --> 00:19:16,800
I know you're just trying to

652
00:19:17,440 --> 00:19:18,600
earn more points.

653
00:19:18,600 --> 00:19:20,280
Yeah, I want to win.

654
00:19:20,280 --> 00:19:21,080
They both get that.

655
00:19:22,760 --> 00:19:23,840
They're a good couple.

656
00:19:24,560 --> 00:19:25,480
No mixed signals.

657
00:19:25,480 --> 00:19:25,880
Exactly.

658
00:19:25,880 --> 00:19:27,080
(Clearly got the spark)

659
00:19:27,080 --> 00:19:28,320
Is this rose?

660
00:19:32,240 --> 00:19:32,990
Nuts.

661
00:19:33,120 --> 00:19:34,240
No, it looks bad.

662
00:19:34,240 --> 00:19:35,120
Don't do that.

663
00:19:35,120 --> 00:19:35,640
Not romantic.

664
00:19:35,840 --> 00:19:37,440
Just hand it over.

665
00:19:37,440 --> 00:19:37,720
Okay?

666
00:19:37,880 --> 00:19:38,320
Don't.

667
00:19:38,420 --> 00:19:39,460
(Worried for him)

668
00:19:40,680 --> 00:19:41,920
We're both so anxious.

669
00:19:41,920 --> 00:19:43,040
Almost blew the whole thing.

670
00:19:43,060 --> 00:19:44,840
(Holding my breath for him)

671
00:19:44,840 --> 00:19:46,160
It's voting time.

672
00:19:46,160 --> 00:19:47,560
Don't tell me someone's leaving.

673
00:19:47,560 --> 00:19:49,120
Chen Yijia, please

674
00:19:49,120 --> 00:19:52,200
proceed to deliver your affection.

675
00:19:54,080 --> 00:19:55,160
All in?

676
00:19:55,160 --> 00:19:55,920
(Yijia > Zizheng)

677
00:19:55,920 --> 00:19:57,440
Compared to yesterday, I'll give

678
00:19:57,440 --> 00:19:58,280
two more weights.

679
00:19:58,280 --> 00:19:59,280
She used them all.

680
00:19:59,280 --> 00:20:00,000
Because

681
00:20:00,340 --> 00:20:00,920
in real life,

682
00:20:00,920 --> 00:20:02,960
things like that almost never happen.

683
00:20:04,440 --> 00:20:06,080
The moment I fell into the water,

684
00:20:06,080 --> 00:20:07,840
I was completely overwhelmed.

685
00:20:07,840 --> 00:20:09,720
A wave of intense

686
00:20:09,720 --> 00:20:11,160
loss of control just hit me.

687
00:20:11,160 --> 00:20:12,280
But someone lifted me up,

688
00:20:12,280 --> 00:20:15,880
which was truly moving.

689
00:20:15,880 --> 00:20:16,640
So at that moment,

690
00:20:16,640 --> 00:20:17,400
I genuinely felt

691
00:20:17,400 --> 00:20:19,440
a deep, indescribable emotion.

692
00:20:19,440 --> 00:20:21,200
It really touched me.

693
00:20:21,200 --> 00:20:21,800
He saved her.

694
00:20:21,800 --> 00:20:22,200
Yeah.

695
00:20:22,200 --> 00:20:24,040
Totally worth giving all votes.

696
00:20:29,080 --> 00:20:30,400
She turned around.

697
00:20:30,400 --> 00:20:31,000
Xiaofan.

698
00:20:31,640 --> 00:20:32,960
Who?

699
00:20:33,440 --> 00:20:34,840
What exactly am I voting for?

700
00:20:35,800 --> 00:20:36,720
I'm losing it.

701
00:20:36,720 --> 00:20:38,040
There was no footage.

702
00:20:38,040 --> 00:20:38,520
Not at all.

703
00:20:38,520 --> 00:20:38,770
No.

704
00:20:38,960 --> 00:20:39,520
Losing it.

705
00:20:39,520 --> 00:20:39,640
Oh.

706
00:20:39,640 --> 00:20:40,040
She's

707
00:20:40,040 --> 00:20:40,440
losing it.

708
00:20:40,440 --> 00:20:40,840
She said.

709
00:20:40,840 --> 00:20:41,760
I'm not sure.

710
00:20:42,220 --> 00:20:43,320
(Before)
She wants to go back.

711
00:20:43,320 --> 00:20:44,320
On our date today,

712
00:20:44,320 --> 00:20:46,120
we didn't talk much

713
00:20:46,120 --> 00:20:46,760
about

714
00:20:46,760 --> 00:20:49,000
ourselves.

715
00:20:49,800 --> 00:20:52,720
Most of it was about the votes

716
00:20:52,720 --> 00:20:54,760
and going over previous plans.

717
00:20:55,680 --> 00:20:56,640
Just trying to get by.

718
00:20:56,640 --> 00:20:57,920
She's not really believing

719
00:20:57,920 --> 00:20:59,360
in being treated as the one and only.

720
00:20:59,360 --> 00:20:59,880
Yeah.

721
00:21:00,240 --> 00:21:00,600
He just

722
00:21:00,600 --> 00:21:01,440
told me

723
00:21:01,440 --> 00:21:03,040
he'll give me all his votes tonight.

724
00:21:03,040 --> 00:21:03,760
Who? Huang Jiawei.

725
00:21:04,640 --> 00:21:06,080
But honestly, why did he tell me?

726
00:21:06,080 --> 00:21:07,000
Yeah.

727
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:08,320
(I hate hearing such things)
So?

728
00:21:09,240 --> 00:21:10,280
Day one, you say all in.

729
00:21:10,280 --> 00:21:11,560
And day two... so what?

730
00:21:11,560 --> 00:21:12,040
Exactly.

731
00:21:12,040 --> 00:21:14,800
Are you hinting at something
I should catch on to?

732
00:21:14,800 --> 00:21:16,000
That's something that girls

733
00:21:16,000 --> 00:21:17,280
would instinctively resist.

734
00:21:17,280 --> 00:21:17,780
(No)
Yeah.

735
00:21:17,780 --> 00:21:18,800
It is.

736
00:21:18,800 --> 00:21:19,400
Right.

737
00:21:19,880 --> 00:21:22,960
All the affections have been delivered.

738
00:21:24,200 --> 00:21:26,320
Now I ask all islanders

739
00:21:26,320 --> 00:21:28,200
head to the square for the gathering.

740
00:21:28,200 --> 00:21:29,120
Everyone.

741
00:21:29,480 --> 00:21:30,840
Are they announcing this in public?

742
00:21:31,770 --> 00:21:32,600
It's getting intense.

743
00:21:32,600 --> 00:21:34,400
That's so harsh.

744
00:21:35,120 --> 00:21:37,080
The one with fewer weights is...

745
00:21:37,600 --> 00:21:38,760
Ye Jiajie.

746
00:21:38,760 --> 00:21:39,600
(2 votes)
Ye Jiajie.

747
00:21:39,600 --> 00:21:40,760
Yi Xiaofan.

748
00:21:40,760 --> 00:21:42,900
(Shocked)

749
00:21:43,040 --> 00:21:44,840
That means...

750
00:21:44,840 --> 00:21:46,800
Yan didn't vote for Xiaofan.

751
00:21:46,800 --> 00:21:48,220
Then who did she give her votes to?

752
00:21:48,220 --> 00:21:50,100
(Zhu Huiyan voted for Huang Jiawei?)
All in?

753
00:21:52,000 --> 00:21:53,320
Yan gave a vote to Zizheng.

754
00:21:53,320 --> 00:21:54,720
That's why Zizheng came in first.

755
00:21:55,280 --> 00:21:56,680
I didn't expect it was Yan.

756
00:21:57,240 --> 00:21:58,760
Yan also voted for Jiajie.

757
00:21:58,760 --> 00:22:01,500
(Ye Jiajie)

758
00:22:01,520 --> 00:22:03,120
See? What Zizheng did today

759
00:22:03,120 --> 00:22:04,720
has earned everyone's respect.

760
00:22:04,720 --> 00:22:05,200
Yeah.

761
00:22:05,200 --> 00:22:06,880
You don't need to hang out

762
00:22:06,880 --> 00:22:07,740
with other girls.

763
00:22:07,740 --> 00:22:09,320
If they admire you, they'll vote for you.

764
00:22:10,360 --> 00:22:11,200
Because

765
00:22:11,200 --> 00:22:12,800
if I package myself up today

766
00:22:13,160 --> 00:22:15,560
just to make you like

767
00:22:15,560 --> 00:22:16,480
that version of me,

768
00:22:17,240 --> 00:22:18,490
then who are you really liking?

769
00:22:19,200 --> 00:22:20,920
He treats himself like a live experiment,

770
00:22:20,920 --> 00:22:22,800
testing it out in person.

771
00:22:22,800 --> 00:22:23,680
Right?

772
00:22:24,480 --> 00:22:26,280
It's raw honesty without fear.

773
00:22:26,280 --> 00:22:27,240
That's a rare mindset.

774
00:22:27,240 --> 00:22:28,200
Period.

775
00:22:28,260 --> 00:22:29,000
(That's me)

776
00:22:29,000 --> 00:22:30,960
He's got one thing absolutely right

777
00:22:30,960 --> 00:22:32,640
that he never hides who he is,

778
00:22:33,120 --> 00:22:34,640
and never puts on a facade.

779
00:22:34,640 --> 00:22:35,600
But I feel like he's...

780
00:22:35,600 --> 00:22:37,860
This wasn't his goal when he first came.

781
00:22:37,860 --> 00:22:39,000
(Against his original intent)

782
00:22:39,000 --> 00:22:40,290
But I think that's just his cover

783
00:22:40,290 --> 00:22:42,240
(Flimsy excuse)
after things went sideways.

784
00:22:42,240 --> 00:22:44,360
But the way he acts...

785
00:22:44,840 --> 00:22:46,400
I'd say it feels genuine.

786
00:22:46,640 --> 00:22:47,360
Almost too real.

787
00:22:48,000 --> 00:22:49,200
Someone could get hurt.

788
00:22:49,200 --> 00:22:50,180
(Uncomfortably real)

789
00:22:51,560 --> 00:22:52,800
Alright.

790
00:22:52,800 --> 00:22:53,960
I hope he's happy.

791
00:22:55,280 --> 00:22:56,080
Let's go up there.

792
00:22:56,080 --> 00:22:57,280
I don't want to stay down here.

793
00:22:57,440 --> 00:22:58,520
Where to?

794
00:22:59,600 --> 00:23:00,760
Wanna sit on the rooftop?

795
00:23:01,560 --> 00:23:02,400
Here.

796
00:23:02,400 --> 00:23:02,660
Okay.

797
00:23:02,660 --> 00:23:03,200
Here's fine.

798
00:23:03,200 --> 00:23:05,100
(Leaving together)
I thought it was over there.

799
00:23:05,360 --> 00:23:06,720
I feel really good today.

800
00:23:06,720 --> 00:23:07,680
Like, really good.

801
00:23:09,600 --> 00:23:11,000
I think he went back to his room.

802
00:23:11,000 --> 00:23:12,250
Didn't he go look for those two?

803
00:23:12,250 --> 00:23:12,880
He went back.

804
00:23:13,880 --> 00:23:15,360
Yeah, he did.

805
00:23:15,360 --> 00:23:16,100
(A lonely figure)

806
00:23:16,560 --> 00:23:18,240
If I get eliminated tomorrow...

807
00:23:18,240 --> 00:23:19,520
No way.

808
00:23:19,520 --> 00:23:20,000
Impossible.

809
00:23:20,000 --> 00:23:20,960
I won't let that happen.

810
00:23:20,960 --> 00:23:21,800
Don't worry.

811
00:23:23,280 --> 00:23:24,080
That line.

812
00:23:24,560 --> 00:23:26,040
He's watching.

813
00:23:27,800 --> 00:23:30,760
He's hesitating about
whether to take a walk.

814
00:23:33,840 --> 00:23:34,560
They left.

815
00:23:36,480 --> 00:23:37,880
You're looking for something to do.

816
00:23:37,880 --> 00:23:38,560
Yeah.

817
00:23:38,900 --> 00:23:40,160
You always have a lot going on.

818
00:23:40,160 --> 00:23:41,400
So I need to do something.

819
00:23:41,400 --> 00:23:42,800
(Feeling jealous)

820
00:23:42,800 --> 00:23:43,480
Right?

821
00:23:43,960 --> 00:23:45,880
You've got another date lined up.

822
00:23:45,880 --> 00:23:47,240
And you're always so busy.

823
00:23:48,080 --> 00:23:48,790
King of jealousy.

824
00:23:49,520 --> 00:23:51,360
Who told you to
pass the ball to someone else?

825
00:23:51,700 --> 00:23:52,880
(Dangerous question)

826
00:23:52,880 --> 00:23:54,720
I've already realized what went wrong.

827
00:23:54,720 --> 00:23:55,920
So tomorrow I'll...

828
00:23:58,000 --> 00:23:59,680
Actually, you had a shot at first place.

829
00:23:59,680 --> 00:24:00,680
Jiayi's good at it too.

830
00:24:00,680 --> 00:24:01,360
Yeah.

831
00:24:02,080 --> 00:24:04,880
It's usually something
guys are expected to do.

832
00:24:04,880 --> 00:24:05,880
And you froze again.

833
00:24:05,880 --> 00:24:07,600
You got shy and flustered again.

834
00:24:07,600 --> 00:24:08,800
But I...

835
00:24:09,480 --> 00:24:11,560
I'll give it my best shot.

836
00:24:11,960 --> 00:24:12,280
So...

837
00:24:12,280 --> 00:24:13,720
I've actually been wanting to

838
00:24:13,720 --> 00:24:15,200
find a chance to talk to you.

839
00:24:15,560 --> 00:24:16,080
But...

840
00:24:16,080 --> 00:24:17,120
You're way too slow.

841
00:24:17,600 --> 00:24:18,760
She said you're too slow.

842
00:24:20,080 --> 00:24:20,680
Alright.

843
00:24:21,240 --> 00:24:23,160
Xuan Cheng still found a way

844
00:24:23,160 --> 00:24:24,920
to show his shyness.

845
00:24:24,920 --> 00:24:27,440
(Looking forward to his change)
His growth is worth waiting for.

846
00:24:27,440 --> 00:24:29,160
(Dating tip 2.0)
Plus, I feel

847
00:24:29,160 --> 00:24:30,440
Jiayi actually noticed everything.

848
00:24:31,280 --> 00:24:33,600
Like when playing on the swing

849
00:24:33,600 --> 00:24:35,360
or the spinning wheel,

850
00:24:35,360 --> 00:24:36,160
he was not there.

851
00:24:36,160 --> 00:24:37,960
And he threw the ball,

852
00:24:37,960 --> 00:24:39,440
but didn't aim it at her.

853
00:24:39,440 --> 00:24:40,200
She noticed it all.

854
00:24:40,380 --> 00:24:42,160
(On the swing)

855
00:24:42,160 --> 00:24:43,320
This is so much fun.

856
00:24:45,280 --> 00:24:46,800
Now let's give the title of

857
00:24:46,800 --> 00:24:47,840
"Regret Guy" to Xuan Cheng.

858
00:24:47,840 --> 00:24:48,760
(Regret Guy)

859
00:24:48,760 --> 00:24:49,920
Got to give it to him.

860
00:24:49,920 --> 00:24:52,040
Now that Jiayi has noticed everything

861
00:24:52,040 --> 00:24:53,720
and actually paid attention to him,

862
00:24:53,720 --> 00:24:54,680
if Xuan Cheng

863
00:24:55,080 --> 00:24:56,920
makes a change, I think Jiayi

864
00:24:56,920 --> 00:24:57,720
would be moved.

865
00:24:58,280 --> 00:24:59,440
(Dating tip 2.0)
Yeah.

866
00:24:59,440 --> 00:24:59,880
A change.

867
00:24:59,880 --> 00:25:01,580
(They could be a couple)
She'll feel special.

868
00:25:01,580 --> 00:25:01,800
Yeah.

869
00:25:01,800 --> 00:25:02,160
Right?

870
00:25:02,160 --> 00:25:03,880
They're washing dishes together now.

871
00:25:03,880 --> 00:25:05,120
From this kitchen scene,

872
00:25:05,120 --> 00:25:07,480
